  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Soften the onion</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ 350°F/ Gas 4.</p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>. Peel and finely chop the <strong>garlic</strong>.</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 8-10 minutes or until softened.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Mash the butternut squash</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> (</span>just enough to cover them) with a pinch of <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>salt</strong></span>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 minutes or until they're tender.</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and mash until smooth.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the risotto</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 700ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1.4L]</span> of <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 minute, stirring to coat the grains in the oil.</p>\n<p>Add <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>1/3</strong> </span>of the <strong>stock</strong> and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it has absorbed.</p>\n<p>Continue to add the stock a little at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 minutes or until the stock has been absorbed and the rice is cooked.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1659.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
