            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make the crispy sage</strong></p>\n<p>Once the risotto is almost done, heat a separate large, wide-based frying pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sage leaves</strong> and cook for 1 minute or until crispy.</p>\n<p>Set aside on a piece of <strong>kitchen paper</strong> to drain the excess oil and season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Reserve the pan for later.</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
